JO  - AMR
SP  - 91
EP  - 103
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper examines the operating characteristics of setup when used as a decision variable in a capacity-constrained production-inventory environment. Within this study, the interrelationships among capacity expansion, order quantity adjustment, and setup time reduction are analyzed, and a model is formulated to evaluate the relative effectiveness of these decision variables. A series of propositions is presented to suggest future directions for research.
AB  - This paper examines the operating characteristics of setup when used as a decision variable in a capacity-constrained production-inventory environment. Within this study, the interrelationships among capacity expansion, order quantity adjustment, and setup time reduction are analyzed, and a model is formulated to evaluate the relative effectiveness of these decision variables. A series of propositions is presented to suggest future directions for research.
