SP  - 133
EP  - 137
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a response by William H. Glick to a commentary on his paper ?Conceptualizing and measuring organizational and psychological climate: Pitfalls in multilevel research.? Glick notes the differences in definitions of organizational climate (OC). One definition classifies OC as a psychological construct, the other defines it as an organizational attribute. He acknowledges that the alternate viewpoints help to identify fundamental differences between two schools of thought in organizational science.
AB  - The article presents a response by William H. Glick to a commentary on his paper ?Conceptualizing and measuring organizational and psychological climate: Pitfalls in multilevel research.? Glick notes the differences in definitions of organizational climate (OC). One definition classifies OC as a psychological construct, the other defines it as an organizational attribute. He acknowledges that the alternate viewpoints help to identify fundamental differences between two schools of thought in organizational science.
