TY  - JOUR
T1  - Configurational and Coactivational Views of Organizational Structure
AU  - Dow, Gregory K.
Y1  - 1988/01/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1988.4306781
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1988.4306781
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 53
EP  - 64
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Two distinct views of organizational structure, configurational and coactivational, are discussed. The configurational view stresses the authoritative coordination of work, whereas the coactivational view emphasizes recurrent patterns of interaction among participants. These two conceptual schemes differ in their stances toward hierarchy, power, and organizational purposiveness. The coactivational view substitutes ?invisible hand? explanations of structure for the intentionalist explanations advanced by configurational theory.
AB  - Two distinct views of organizational structure, configurational and coactivational, are discussed. The configurational view stresses the authoritative coordination of work, whereas the coactivational view emphasizes recurrent patterns of interaction among participants. These two conceptual schemes differ in their stances toward hierarchy, power, and organizational purposiveness. The coactivational view substitutes ?invisible hand? explanations of structure for the intentionalist explanations advanced by configurational theory.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1988.4306781
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1988.4306781
