T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 129
EP  - 132
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a commentary on the paper ?Conceptualizing and measuring organizational and psychological climate: Pitfalls in multilevel research,? by W. H. Glick. The authors note that Glick's paper contains some inconsistencies. They explain that it is difficult to understand how Glick defined organizational climate (OC) as a nonpsychological, organizational variable that is different from a shared assignment of psychological meaning. The authors contend that methodological discussion and decisions should follow questions such as whether it makes sense to aggregate a psychological variable to a situational level of analysis.
AB  - The article presents a commentary on the paper ?Conceptualizing and measuring organizational and psychological climate: Pitfalls in multilevel research,? by W. H. Glick. The authors note that Glick's paper contains some inconsistencies. They explain that it is difficult to understand how Glick defined organizational climate (OC) as a nonpsychological, organizational variable that is different from a shared assignment of psychological meaning. The authors contend that methodological discussion and decisions should follow questions such as whether it makes sense to aggregate a psychological variable to a situational level of analysis.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1988.4306808
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1988.4306808
Y2  - 2026/04/24
